external_knowledge:
- "Crossed the threshold of responsiveness" refers to reaction times (RT) >= 0.8;
- "Average speeds in the competitive race of performance" means the average RT values, indicating model performance;
- The goal is to identify the model names and versions where their performance meets or exceeds a specified standard.

sql:
SELECT model_id, AVG(rt) AS average_reaction_time
FROM performance_metrics
GROUP BY model_id;

